&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Associate Director of Nursing - Medicine &amp; Urgent Care&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently seeking a candidate with strong leadership and management experience to join our team in the Division of Medicine and Urgent Care. As one of two Associate Directors of Nursing you will support the Divisional Director of Nursing, AHPs and Quality in the leadership of all nursing and support staff as well as working as part of the sub-divisional triumvirate team to deliver the strategic plan for the care groups under your leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work at our North Middlesex University Hospital Site covering a number of acute and general medical wards and services. You will have opportunity to work as part of an exciting and motivated divisional team in driving change and high standards, whilst leading with compassion and integrity. You will also be part of the Senior Manager on Call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of the senior nursing leadership team you will help shape the future of nursing at the organisation and ensure that the voice of nursing is heard from ward to board. With a strong emphasis on clinical quality and patient experience this role is pivotal in the delivery of both the Divisional and Trust strategic view.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Richard Hughes, Divisional Director of Nursing, Allied Health Professions and Quality via his PA Jayne Barry Email: jayne.barry@nhs.net Tel No: 020 8887 3287&lt;/p&gt;
